author: kfogel
msg: Make cvs2svn handle unexpected characters in metadata more robustly:
* tools/cvs2svn/cvs2svn.py
(Commit.commit): Tell unicode conversion to replace unknown
characters with the official Unicode replacement character U+FFFD,
but leave a note about making this behavior optional later on.
Also, catch unicode conversion exceptions and print useful errors,
though such exceptions are much less likely now that we replace.

author: kfogel
msg: Make 'svnadmin load' output slightly friendlier:
* subversion/libsvn_repos/load.c
(close_revision): Print more concise revision messages for the
common case of loading into an empty repository.
* subversion/tests/clients/cmdline/svntest/main.py
(copy_repos): Expect the new output.

author: kfogel
msg: People would misunderstand directory out-of-date messages, because the
error message was claiming "file":
* subversion/libsvn_ra_dav/commit.c
(checkout_resource): Say "file or directory" in error message, don't
just assume "file".
This is an empty revision for padding.
